Ramen Rating Analysis and Predictor¶

In this project, we will be using Ramen Rater's The Big List dataset (https://www.theramenrater.com/resources-2/the-list/) to analyze ramen feedback and create a predictive model on the best noodle flavor, through machine learning. From its variety info, we will create different categorizations such as "spicy", "beef", "chicken", and "seafood" to observe preferences. Moreover, we will create a classifier using Dummy Classifier, Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, and Random Forest.

This analysis is made with UpLevel's Code-Along sessions.

In [9]:
# Clean the Stars values

# 4.5/5 -> 4.5
# 5/2.5 -> 2.5
# 3.5/2.5 -> 2.5
# 4.25/5 -> 4.25

df['Stars'] = df['Stars'].replace('4.5/5', 4.5)
df['Stars'] = df['Stars'].replace('5/2.5', 2.5)
df['Stars'] = df['Stars'].replace('3.5/2.5', 2.5)
df['Stars'] = df['Stars'].replace('4.25/5', 4.25)

# many adjectives
# make Spicy category based on the token (flavor)
is_spicy = []

hot_flavor = ["spicy",
             "curry",
             "hot",
             "tom",
             "chili",
             "chilli",
             "kari",
             "pedas",
             "laksa"]

# categories reviews from original data set which contains selected token flavors
for variety in df['Variety'].str.lower():
    if any(flavor in variety for flavor in hot_flavor):
        is_spicy.append(1)
    else:
        is_spicy.append(0)
        
df['isSpicy'] = is_spicy
df

# make chicken category based on the token (flavor)

has_chicken = []

        has_chicken.append(0)

In [49]:
# import mann-whitney u test for stats test
from scipy.stats import mannwhitneyu # for data not normally distributed
In [50]:
mannwhitneyu(spicy_df['Stars'],
            nonspicy_df['Stars'])

# pvalue < 0.05; very small - stars in spicy is definitely different from non-spicy
Out[50]:
MannwhitneyuResult(statistic=1525932.5, pvalue=1.2489797441151044e-07)

        new_brand.append(brand)
    else:
        new_brand.append("Other")

dummy.fit(X_train, y_train)
dummy_pred = dummy.predict(X_test)
